Some angry mob on yesterday went wild in Kogi, set ablaze police barracks, over an alleged killing of a boy by a policeman in Kabba town of Kogi State. Earlier, the alleged killing of a young boy by a yet to be identified Police officer sparked protests in Kabba town yesterday morning. At the time of filing this report, a team of Mobile Policemen and men of the Nigerian Army had been deployed to Kabba town.   Alumona, AAAN Vice President, becomes APCON Fellow     2023: IBB wise after the fact     Onaiyekan to Buhari: Allow Nigerians to pick your successor…   Sources in the community said the situation had been put under control. The boy was alleged to have taken a sachet of pure water from the Policeman’s man’s car to drink but later had an argument with the Policeman before he was killed. - Advertisement - The Kogi State Commissioner of Police CP Edward Egbuka confirmed the latest development to journalists yesterday afternoon. He said the command was currently investigating the matter.